After the 5th, 6th and 7th in the following lines;


"Men would be angels, angels would be Gods.

Aſpiring to be Gods, if angels fell;

Aſpiring to be angels, men rebel."
                  POPE.

And it very frequently happens that either the ſenſe or harmony or both require two or more ſemi-pauſes; as,
"To him no high, no low, no great, no ſmall;
He fills, he bounds, connects, and equals all." POPE.
